<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-101-082 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 142 671</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  July 29 1991 v20 n21p2(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Alphatype's UK dealer goes bankrupt; U.S. firm seeks newrepresentation. (Alphatype Europe)(The Latest Word)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Alphatype Corp. (Finance).andO;Topic:     BankruptcyEuropeUnited KingdomDealers and AgentsFinancial AnalysisDesktop PublishingAdd-In/On SoftwareSoftware PackagesSoftware PublishersPage Description LanguagesFonts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Alphatype Europe, which has served as Alphatype's dealer in England andScandinavia, is undergoing bankruptcy proceedings under the UK Insolvency Actof 1986.andP;  The dealership, which was formerly called Alphatype UK, is owned byTim Wood.andM;A meeting of creditors was called by Wood and Phil Jones, the two directors,to discuss procedures regarding secured creditors.andP;  Following that meeting,which took place on July 11 in Buckinghamshire, Alphatype said it wouldannounce its plans for handling sales and support in England and some partsof Europe.andM;Alphatype said it would reestablish a service organization.andP;  It currently hasmore than 100 customers in England.andM;Besides the UK company, Alphatype has active dealerships in Greece and inCanada.andP;  Plans call for representation in Italy, Spain and France.andP;  Sales inthe U.S.andP;  are through a direct sales force.andM;Alphatype said that about half of its sales in the last year took placeoutside the U.S., with about one-fourth of the non-U.S.andP;  sales occurring inthe UK.andM;U.S.andP;  company not affected.andP;  Alphatype said the failure of the Europeancompany did not reflect the status of its U.S.andP;  operation, which is &quot;holdingits own&quot; in spite of the overall weak economy.andM;Type 1 fonts.andP;  Alphatype also announced that it is ready to begin testing itstype library in PostScript Type 1 format.andP;  Taking advantage of Adobe'sMultiple Master technology, it will produce one library using different-sizedoriginal font designs to generate different sizes of type.andP;  We understandthere will be between three and five separate cuts in various sizes for eachtypeface.andM;There also will be a &quot;desktop&quot; version of the library that uses a singlemaster for all sizes.andM;Fonts are available in Macintosh, PC and Next Computer formats.andO;</TEXT></DOC>